---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Constitution Atlas" description="About the Constitution Atlas project.">
	<section class="page-intro">
		<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
		<h1>A constitutional reference platform, not a generic news site.</h1>
		<p class="page-intro__summary">
			Constitution Atlas is designed as a structured reading system for the Indian Constitution. Evergreen
			reference pages explain provisions, cases, and amendments. Live explainers connect those materials to
			ongoing public debates.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="page-copy prose">
		<h2>Editorial direction</h2>
		<p>
			The project is built to privilege constitutional relevance over volume. Not every political event belongs on
			the site. Only issues that raise identifiable constitutional questions should be published as live explainers.
		</p>
		<h2>Who it serves</h2>
		<p>
			The primary audience is students, journalists, policy readers, and citizens who want a neutral, source-based
			entry point into constitutional law.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
